Difference between document and windows object

Document Object:
1.The document object represent a web page that is loaded in the browser. By accessing the document object,we can access the element in the HTML page. 
With the help of document objects, we can add dynamic content to our web page. The document object can be accessed with a window.document or just document
2.All the tags, elements with attributes in HTML are part of the document.
3.It is loaded inside the window.

Syntax:
document.property_name;
example:
document.title :  will return the title of the document

Window Object: 
1.The window object is the topmost object of the DOM hierarchy. It represents a browser window or frame that displays the contents of the webpage. 
Whenever a window appears on the screen to display the contents of the document, the window object is created. 
2.Global objects, functions, and variables of JavaScript are members of the window object.
3.It is the very first object that is loaded in the browser.

Syntax:
window.property_name;
example:
window.innerHeight : will return the height of the content area of the browser
